Use ⁨hello-world⁩ to explore layered greetings across config, env, and CLI

Usage: Usage:
⁨hello-world⁩ [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Visit --help for details.

Commands:
  greet       Prints a friendly greeting using any configured templates.
  take-leave  Describes how the farewell workflow proceeds for the recipient.
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -c, --config <PATH>
          Path to the configuration file

  -r, --recipient <NAME>
          Recipient of the greeting when supplied on the CLI

  -s, --salutation <WORD>
          Replacement salutations supplied on the CLI

      --is-excited
          Enables an enthusiastic delivery mode from the CLI

      --is-quiet
          Enables a quiet delivery mode from the CLI

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
